    <!-- EV Range Basics -->
    <section id="basics" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">EV Range Basics: How It Works</h2>

      <Card className="p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">What Is EV Range?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200 mb-4">
          <strong>EV Range</strong> is the distance an electric vehicle can travel on a fully charged battery before it needs recharging. It's equivalent to asking "how far can a diesel car go on a full tank?"
        </p>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/30 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-sm">
            <strong>Simple Formula:</strong><br/>
            Range (km) = Battery Capacity (kWh) √∑ Energy Consumption (kWh/km) √ó Efficiency
          </p>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Card className="p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">How EVs Store and Use Energy</h3>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <Battery className="h-5 w-5 text-green-600" />
              Battery Pack Structure
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Kia Carens EV:</strong> 70 kWh lithium-ion battery pack</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>BYD E-MAX 7:</strong> 71.8 kWh Blade Battery (LFP)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Battery is mounted in floor (low center of gravity)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Contains hundreds of individual cells</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Thermal management keeps optimal temperature</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <Zap className="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-600" />
              Energy Flow During Drive
            </h4>
            <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li>‚Ä¢ Battery ‚Üí Motor (electricity powers wheels)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Motor converts 90%+ of energy to motion (diesel: 35%)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ When braking: Motor ‚Üí Battery (regen)</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ AC, lights, infotainment use small % of battery</li>
              <li>‚Ä¢ Computer optimizes energy usage in real-time</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Card className="p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Understanding Battery Percentage</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p><strong>100% battery</strong> = Fully charged, maximum range available</p>
          <p><strong>80% battery</strong> = Typical "full" charge for daily use (extends battery life)</p>
          <p><strong>50% battery</strong> = Half range remaining, still plenty for most trips</p>
          <p><strong>20% battery</strong> = Low battery warning, time to charge soon</p>
          <p><strong>10% battery</strong> = Very low, reduced performance (turtle mode)</p>
          <p><strong>0% battery</strong> = Not actually empty! 5-10% reserve for safety</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/30 p-4 rounded-lg mt-4">
